#week-title("Four", "Review & Integration: The Doctrine of Correspondences")

=== Core Teaching

This week serves as a moment of integration. The *Doctrine of Correspondences* is
not merely a system of symbols; it is a practical map for the alchemist. By
recognizing the signatures of nature, you begin to see the "One Thing" acting
through diverse forms.

Whether you are looking at the shape of a leaf or drawing a Tarot card, you are
interacting with the same universal intelligence. The goal of this month has been
to develop the *Hermetic eye* — the ability to see the invisible forces behind the
visible world.

=== Topics This Week

- Synthesis of plant signatures and planetary archetypes
- The interconnectedness of the Triune Discipline (Alchemy, Astrology, Qabalah)
- Reviewing the first quarter's progress

#inner-work[
  *The Tarot Journal & Final Grouping*

  Review your first Tarot practice from Week 2. Re-examine your groupings of the
  Major Arcana. Having assigned keywords in Week 3, would you change your
  groupings now?

  Record your final keyword list in your Tarot journal. This journal is a sacred
  record of your developing intuition and symbolic literacy. Use it to record
  any insights that arise during your daily meditation or nature vigils.
]

=== Weekly Assignment

Write a one-page reflection on the *Doctrine of Correspondences*. Choose one
planet and describe its manifestation across three kingdoms: its metal, its
preferred herb, and its influence on the human body or psyche. How does
recognizing these links change your relationship to that planet?

